Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State has arrived at the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, headquarters in Abuja. Okowa arrived at the party’s headquarters to attend the PDP’s Vice Presidential screening. The governor was welcomed into the building with the words ‘congratulations’ by members of the party. DAILY POST reported that the PDP presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar may pick Okowa as his running mate. Okowa and Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, are among the names being mentioned as Atiku’s likely running mates.